<doc id="149294" wikidata="Q21660706" url="?curid=149294" title="Bernstein">
<text>Bernstein is a common surname of German origin, meaning &quot;amber&quot; (literally &quot;burn stone&quot;). The name is used by both Germans and Jews, although it is most common among people of Ashkenazi Jewish heritage. The German pronunciation is , but in English, it is pronounced either as or .

==Notable people sharing the surname &quot;Bernstein&quot;==
===A–H===
* Aaron Bernstein (1812–1884), German short story writer and historian
* Abe Bernstein (1892–1968), American mobster
* Abraham Bernstein (disambiguation), several people
