<doc id="149305" wikidata="Q5091708" url="?curid=149305" title="Chepi">
<text>Chepi is a ghost or fairy in the mythology of the Narragansett tribe of Native Americans from the Narragansett Bay region of Rhode Island, Connecticut, and eastern Massachusetts. Chepi is a spirit of the dead who shared knowledge with medicine people in dreams or visions. Chepi could be called upon by the &quot;pawwaw&quot; or medicine person, to destroy an enemy as an avenging entity.

